org.opengis.cite.kml2.validation

Class GeoExtentValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opengis.cite.kml2.validation.GeoExtentValidator

  • public class GeoExtentValidator
extends Object
    Validates the content of an element that represents a geographic extent (that is, it substitutes directly or indirectly for kml:AbstractExtentGroup). The allowed elements include the following, although not all are permitted in every context:
    • kml:LatLonBox
    • kml:LatLonAltBox
    • kml:LatLonQuad

      • validateQuadrilateral

        public boolean validateQuadrilateral(Node latlonQuad)
        Checks that a kml:LatLonQuad element has valid coordinates and satisfies the following additional constraints:
        1. the four coordinate tuples are specified in counter-clockwise order (the interior is to the left of the boundary curve), with the first coordinate corresponding to the lower-left corner of the overlayed image;
        2. the quadrilateral is convex (every interior angle <= 180 degrees).
        Parameters:
        latlonQuad - A kml:LatLonQuad element.
        Returns:
        true if all constraints are satisfied; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        "ATC-103: Valid geometry coordinates", "ATC-149: LatLonQuad coordinates"

      • validateBox

        boolean validateBox(Node boxNode)
        Validates a bounding box. The content of a kml:LatLon[Alt]Box element must satisfy all of the following constraints:
        1. kml:north > kml:south;
        2. kml:east > kml:west;
        3. kml:minAltitude <= kml:maxAltitude;
        4. if kml:minAltitude and kml:maxAltitude are both present, then kml:altitudeMode does not have the value "clampToGround".

        Some additional constraints were introduced in KML 2.3 with the longitude range extension (to ± 360):

        • kml:east - kml:west <= 360 (non-self-overlap)
        • if |kml:west| > 180 or |kml:east| > 180, then kml:east > 0 and kml:west < 180 (uniqueness)
        Parameters:
        boxNode - An Element node that contains a bounding box element (kml:LatLon[Alt]Box).
        Returns:
        true if the box satisfies all constraints; false otherwise.
